-- ADB Funds Help Colombo to Replace Aged Sewage Pipes, Mirror Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-07-07T10:16:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-07/adb-funds-help-colombo-to-replace-aged-sewage-pipes-mirror-says.html
Asian Development Bank funds will
help Sri Lanka’s capital and its suburbs install new lines and
replace 70-year-old sewer pipes in a $116 million wastewater
project, the  Daily Mirror  said, citing the Colombo Municipal
Council’s chief engineer. Contractors have begun work on the
wastewater project at two sites near the sea, the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
